 a time projection chamber which thus contains about 3.6 t of\n$^{136}$Xe. Here, we show that its projected half-life sensitivity is\n$2.4\\times10^{27}\\,$yr, using a fiducial volume of 5t of natural xenon and\n10$\\,$yr of operation with a background rate of less than\n0.2$~$events/(t$\\cdot$yr) in the energy region of interest. This sensitivity is\nbased on a detailed Monte Carlo simulation study of the background and event\ntopologies in the large, homogeneous target. DARWIN will be comparable in its\nscience reach to dedicated double beta decay experiments using xenon enriched\nin $^{136}$Xe.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 25 Mar 2020 18:02:11 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 7 Sep 2020 17:42:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-08"}
